percolating interest in the form.

00:50:10.510 --> 00:50:14.190
And I always feel I'm incredibly
lucky that I seem like I'm

00:50:14.190 --> 00:50:18.870
at the door a lot for book
festivals and situations like that

00:50:18.870 --> 00:50:22.800
where the first interesting comics
it finally breaks through and I get

00:50:22.800 --> 00:50:25.150
to go talk at a book festival

00:50:25.150 --> 00:50:28.910
or in this case teach
students graphic novels.

00:50:28.910 --> 00:50:33.150
And it's -- I happen to do a
single page comic every week.

00:50:33.150 --> 00:50:35.800
One of my students said it was
the hardest class that he had

00:50:35.800 --> 00:50:38.660
in all his time at Harvard
and I was like sorry,

00:50:38.660 --> 00:50:41.960
it's the same class I teach at the
School of Visual Arts you know.

00:50:41.960 --> 00:50:46.230
But it is so brilliant, the
students are so great to teach

00:50:46.230 --> 00:50:49.390
that the five hour commute
each way once a week

00:50:49.390 --> 00:50:52.190
from New York is totally
worth it to me.

00:50:52.190 --> 00:50:54.570
I'm giddy about going up there

00:50:54.570 --> 00:50:59.980
and my class is four hours
long and I run out of time.

00:50:59.980 --> 00:51:03.030
It's, you know, I can't
explain it completely.

00:51:03.030 --> 00:51:06.340
I used to have a much shorter
class and I ran out of things

00:51:06.340 --> 00:51:10.160
in the first half hour, but the
students just provide a lot.

00:51:10.160 --> 00:51:14.540
I have 12 students in the class
and I actually have to select them,

00:51:14.540 --> 00:51:16.990
which is another tremendous boon.

00:51:16.990 --> 00:51:20.880
So up to 40 students will apply for
the class and then I interview all

00:51:20.880 --> 00:51:26.090
of them and then pick 12 and 12 is
the right number for four hours.

00:51:26.090 --> 00:51:30.510
And I have them do assignments
that are things like based

00:51:30.510 --> 00:51:33.970
on a dream that they had.

00:51:33.970 --> 00:51:36.960
Interview somebody, so
there's comics journalism.

00:51:36.960 --> 00:51:44.180
Autobiography and social
content and I keep shifting it.

00:51:44.180 --> 00:51:46.410
There was a long time where
in my class I had them say

00:51:46.410 --> 00:51:50.100
where were you 9/11 and
I watch progressively.

00:51:50.100 --> 00:51:53.060
Let's see my mommy brought me
some cookies and I don't remember

00:51:53.060 --> 00:51:56.860
and like okay, time to
drop that one what's next.

00:51:56.860 --> 00:52:02.260
So it's an evolving thing in that
way which is exciting for me too.

00:52:03.770 --> 00:52:05.570
Yes.

