they're humans yeah, okay got it.

00:53:04.250 --> 00:53:05.580
And it turns out yes they are,

00:53:05.580 --> 00:53:09.470
they are hard workers
that's the notable thing.

00:53:09.470 --> 00:53:12.270
They don't tend to miss class and
they tend to do all the assignments

00:53:12.270 --> 00:53:13.720
which doesn't happen as often

00:53:13.720 --> 00:53:17.710
in my other classes,
but generally speaking.

00:53:17.710 --> 00:53:21.570
And it's really the future
of comics to me are people

00:53:21.570 --> 00:53:23.760
who are coming from
other disciplines.

00:53:23.760 --> 00:53:25.710
It's one of the things that's
happened with World War 3 is

00:53:25.710 --> 00:53:28.670
that we've gotten a lot more
women [inaudible] my class

00:53:28.670 --> 00:53:32.290
of 12 has 2 guys and it is so great

00:53:32.290 --> 00:53:36.540
because the women will
lead the charge

00:53:36.540 --> 00:53:38.480
into what's happening in the form.

00:53:38.480 --> 00:53:42.820
And people from various
backgrounds not just a bunch

00:53:42.820 --> 00:53:44.750
of nerdy white guys.

00:53:44.750 --> 00:53:49.390 position:56%
I've been going to comic conventions
my whole life since I was 11.

00:53:49.390 --> 00:53:55.680
It used to be literally all guys
and pretty much all white guys

00:53:55.680 --> 00:54:01.230
and that going to comic conventions
now the dynamic has changed

00:54:01.230 --> 00:54:06.960
dramatically and as a result the
material that's being made has

00:54:06.960 --> 00:54:08.260
changed dramatically.

00:54:08.260 --> 00:54:09.920
And if you're not a comic reader,

00:54:09.920 --> 00:54:14.320
just with a little searching you
can find something that will touch

00:54:14.320 --> 00:54:19.610
on something that interests
you that from all areas.

00:54:19.610 --> 00:54:25.380
There's civil rights
movement done in comics,

00:54:25.380 --> 00:54:30.700 position:56%
a lot of gay lesbian subject matter.

00:54:30.700 --> 00:54:33.850
In fact, that seems to be
a huge arc I'm noticing

00:54:33.850 --> 00:54:37.050
from the last alternative
convention I went to,

00:54:37.050 --> 00:54:39.320
more gay superheroes
and things like that.

00:54:39.320 --> 00:54:41.670
But really pretty much everything.

00:54:41.670 --> 00:54:44.330
There's tremendous journalism
being done in comics.

00:54:44.330 --> 00:54:51.060
Joe Sacco is an artist he's
tackled the Palestinian situation

00:54:51.060 --> 00:54:57.630
and Sarajevo and India
and you name it.

00:54:57.630 --> 00:55:01.980
And then you have, you know,
these pillars like Maus

00:55:01.980 --> 00:55:05.990
that tackled the Holocaust, which
was obviously a huge breakthrough.

00:55:05.990 --> 00:55:10.240
But there's subsequently been
a lot of other work by people

00:55:10.240 --> 00:55:12.760
with a wide range of backgrounds.

00:55:12.760 --> 00:55:18.520
And so if read at all you can
find something that will touch

00:55:18.520 --> 00:55:21.560
on something that you will be
probably very interested in.

00:55:21.560 --> 00:55:25.640
Fun Homes is a fairly recent
autobiography that was made

00:55:25.640 --> 00:55:27.010
into a play I saw recently.

00:55:27.010 --> 00:55:32.820
It was a brilliant, it won the Tony
award best play with good reason.

